label.value: miscellaneous plant or system operator
chemical plant or system operator

definition.value: Control or operate entire chemical processes or system of machines.

label.value: gas plant operator

definition.value: Distribute or process gas for utility companies and others by controlling compressors to maintain specified pressures on main pipelines.

label.value: petroleum pump system operator, refinery operator, or gauger

definition.value: Operate or control petroleum refining or processing units. May specialize in controlling manifold and pumping systems, gauging or testing oil in storage tanks, or regulating the flow of oil into pipelines.

label.value: plant or system operator, all other

definition.value: All plant and system operators not listed separately.

label.value: biofuels processing technician

definition.value: Calculate, measure, load, mix, and process refined feedstock with additives in fermentation or reaction process vessels and monitor production process. Perform, and keep records of, plant maintenance, repairs, and safety inspections.

label.value: other production occupation
chemical processing machine setter, operator, or tender
chemical equipment operator or tender

definition.value: Operate or tend equipment to control chemical changes or reactions in the processing of industrial or consumer products. Equipment used includes devulcanizers, steam-jacketed kettles, and reactor vessels.

label.value: separating, filtering, clarifying, precipitating, or still machine setter, operator, or tender

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend continuous flow or vat-type equipment; filter presses; shaker screens; centrifuges; condenser tubes; precipitating, fermenting, or evaporating tanks; scrubbing towers; or batch stills. These machines extract, sort, or separate liquids, gases, or solids from other materials to recover a refined product. Includes dairy processing equipment operators.

label.value: crushing, grinding, polishing, mixing, or blending worker
crushing, grinding, or polishing machine setter, operator, or tender

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend machines to crush, grind, or polish materials, such as coal, glass, grain, stone, food, or rubber.

label.value: grinding or polishing worker, hand

definition.value: Grind, sand, or polish, using hand tools or hand-held power tools, a variety of metal, wood, stone, clay, plastic, or glass objects. Includes chippers, buffers, and finishers.

label.value: mixing or blending machine setter, operator, or tender

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend machines to mix or blend materials, such as chemicals, tobacco, liquids, color pigments, or explosive ingredients.

label.value: cutting worker
cutter or trimmer, hand

definition.value: Use hand tools or hand-held power tools to cut and trim a variety of manufactured items, such as carpet, fabric, stone, glass, or rubber.

label.value: cutting or slicing machine setter, operator, or tender

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend machines that cut or slice materials, such as glass, stone, cork, rubber, tobacco, food, paper, or insulating material.

label.value: extruding, forming, pressing, or compacting machine setter, operator, or tender (broad)
extruding, forming, pressing, or compacting machine setter, operator, or tender

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend machines, such as glass-forming machines, plodder machines, and tuber machines, to shape and form products such as glassware, food, rubber, soap, brick, tile, clay, wax, tobacco, or cosmetics.

label.value: furnace, Kiln, oven, drier, or Kettle operator or tender (broad)
furnace, kiln, oven, drier, or kettle operator or tender

definition.value: Operate or tend heating equipment other than basic metal, plastic, or food processing equipment. Includes activities such as annealing glass, drying lumber, curing rubber, removing moisture from materials, or boiling soap.

label.value: inspector, tester, sorter, sampler, or weigher (broad)
inspector, tester, sorter, sampler, or weigher

definition.value: Inspect, test, sort, sample, or weigh nonagricultural raw materials or processed, machined, fabricated, or assembled parts or products for defects, wear, and deviations from specifications. May use precision measuring instruments and complex test equipment.

label.value: jeweler or precious stone or metal worker (broad)
jeweler or precious stone or metal worker

definition.value: Design, fabricate, adjust, repair, or appraise jewelry, gold, silver, other precious metals, or gems.

label.value: gem or diamond worker

definition.value: Fabricate, finish, or evaluate the quality of gems and diamonds used in jewelry or industrial tools.

label.value: dental or ophthalmic laboratory technician or medical appliance technician
dental laboratory technician

definition.value: Construct and repair full or partial dentures or dental appliances.

label.value: medical appliance technician

definition.value: Construct, maintain, or repair medical supportive devices such as braces, orthotics and prosthetic devices, joints, arch supports, and other surgical and medical appliances.

label.value: ophthalmic laboratory technician

definition.value: Cut, grind, and polish eyeglasses, contact lenses, or other precision optical elements. Assemble and mount lenses into frames or process other optical elements. Includes precision lens polishers or grinders, centerer-edgers, and lens mounters.

label.value: packaging or filling machine operator or tender (broad)
packaging or filling machine operator or tender

definition.value: Operate or tend machines to prepare industrial or consumer products for storage or shipment. Includes cannery workers who pack food products.

label.value: painting worker
painting, coating, or decorating worker

definition.value: Paint, coat, or decorate articles, such as furniture, glass, plateware, pottery, jewelry, toys, books, or leather.

label.value: coating, painting, or spraying machine setter, operator, or tender

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend spraying or rolling machines to coat or paint any of a wide variety of products, including glassware, cloth, ceramics, metal, plastic, paper, or wood, with lacquer, silver, copper, rubber, varnish, glaze, enamel, oil, or rust-proofing materials. Includes painters of transportation vehicles such as painters in auto body repair facilities.

label.value: semiconductor processing technician (broad)
semiconductor processing technician

definition.value: Perform any or all of the following functions in the manufacture of electronic semiconductors: load semiconductor material into furnace; saw formed ingots into segments; load individual segment into crystal growing chamber and monitor controls; locate crystal axis in ingot using x-ray equipment and saw ingots into wafers; and clean, polish, and load wafers into series of special purpose furnaces, chemical baths, and equipment used to form circuitry and change conductive properties.

label.value: photographic process worker or processing machine operator (broad)
photographic process worker or processing machine operator

definition.value: Perform work involved in developing and processing photographic images from film or digital media. May perform precision tasks such as editing photographic negatives and prints.

label.value: computer numerically controlled tool operator or programmer
computer numerically controlled tool operator

definition.value: Operate computer-controlled tools, machines, or robots to machine or process parts, tools, or other work pieces made of metal, plastic, wood, stone, or other materials. May also set up and maintain equipment.

label.value: computer numerically controlled tool programmer

definition.value: Develop programs to control machining or processing of materials by automatic machine tools, equipment, or systems. May also set up, operate, or maintain equipment.

label.value: miscellaneous production worker
adhesive bonding machine operator or tender

definition.value: Operate or tend bonding machines that use adhesives to join items for further processing or to form a completed product. Processes include joining veneer sheets into plywood; gluing paper; or joining rubber and rubberized fabric parts, plastic, simulated leather, or other materials.

label.value: cleaning, washing, or metal pickling equipment operator or tender

definition.value: Operate or tend machines to wash or clean products, such as barrels or kegs, glass items, tin plate, food, pulp, coal, plastic, or rubber, to remove impurities.

label.value: cooling or freezing equipment operator or tender

definition.value: Operate or tend equipment such as cooling and freezing units, refrigerators, batch freezers, and freezing tunnels, to cool or freeze products, food, blood plasma, and chemicals.

label.value: etcher or engraver

definition.value: Engrave or etch metal, wood, rubber, or other materials. Includes such workers as etcher-circuit processors, pantograph engravers, and silk screen etchers.

label.value: molder, shaper, or caster, except metal or plastic

definition.value: Mold, shape, form, cast, or carve products such as food products, figurines, tile, pipes, and candles consisting of clay, glass, plaster, concrete, stone, or combinations of materials.

label.value: stone cutter or carver, manufacturing

definition.value: Cut or carve stone according to diagrams and patterns.

label.value: glass blower, molder, bender, or finisher

definition.value: Shape molten glass according to patterns.
